WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:02.501
[Violet] <i> Previously on</i>
Queen Sugar...

00:02.578 --> 00:03.585
[Micah] <i> I want to create</i>
<i> something for us</i>

00:03.662 --> 00:05.379
in Web3 definitively black.

00:05.381 --> 00:07.589
I'm gonna really need to delve
into your creative portfolio.

00:07.591 --> 00:08.674
I'm ready for that.

00:08.676 --> 00:11.427
Aunt Martha crossed over
last month.

00:11.429 --> 00:13.178
[Nova] <i> I should have been</i>
<i> more in tune</i>

00:13.255 --> 00:15.305
<i> with everything</i>
<i> on my mother's side</i>
<i> of the family.</i>

00:15.307 --> 00:17.891
I've been on an island
loving you.

00:17.893 --> 00:20.477
-And you've been
struggling to love me.
-Dominic.

00:20.479 --> 00:22.521
I don't want him
being surprised
if he finds out about Chase.

00:22.523 --> 00:24.565
This is so unnecessary.

00:24.567 --> 00:26.567
-Where is this coming from?
-It's coming from my gut!

00:26.569 --> 00:28.402
Should we think
about fostering again?

00:29.905 --> 00:31.613
[hopeful music playing]

00:37.580 --> 00:40.122
Is all this really necessary?

00:40.124 --> 00:43.709
I mean, it hasn't changed
since you were here last.

00:44.253 --> 00:45.878
Standard practice.

00:45.880 --> 00:47.504
I have to make sure
everything's in order

00:47.548 --> 00:49.465
before we assign you a child.

00:51.469 --> 00:53.427
Oh, sorry. [laughs nervously]

00:55.723 --> 00:57.097
[hums]

01:03.606 --> 01:05.522
-[hushed whispers]
-Oh, no worries

01:05.557 --> 01:07.441
about the sherry
laying around anymore.

01:07.443 --> 01:09.693
We... We took the notes
that you gave us
the last time.

01:09.695 --> 01:12.029
We just kicked it up.
[chuckles]

01:16.077 --> 01:19.536
Uh, well you can see
that we just put in
one bed this time.

01:19.538 --> 01:20.746
But we saved the other one

01:20.748 --> 01:22.706
in case
another child needs us.

01:23.417 --> 01:25.793
And um, we...
We're gonna paint.

01:27.505 --> 01:30.005
Look, I know
y'all are good people.

01:30.091 --> 01:32.132
I saw how you took care
of the Avila boys.

01:32.209 --> 01:33.634
But you won't know
the kid this time

01:33.710 --> 01:35.302
and there is a process.

01:35.304 --> 01:38.597
Look Miss Carmichael,
we respect that.

01:39.558 --> 01:40.933
But this right here.

01:42.061 --> 01:44.353
This is the most important
thing to us right now.

01:46.023 --> 01:47.940
Okay, I'm approving you.

01:48.567 --> 01:50.016
You are now officially
on the roster

01:50.018 --> 01:52.444
as permanent foster parents
in the state of Louisiana.

01:52.446 --> 01:55.614
I'll turn in my report
and you'll be notified
about assignments.

01:55.616 --> 01:58.075
Could be as early as 72 hours

01:58.119 --> 02:00.327
for as long
as 90 days or more.

02:00.329 --> 02:01.703
So be patient,

02:02.873 --> 02:04.414
but be ready.

02:04.458 --> 02:07.501
Okay, now do you know
if we'll get a girl or a boy?

02:07.503 --> 02:10.337
[chuckles] I won't know
until there's a need.

02:10.339 --> 02:12.113
You know,
it doesn't even matter.

02:12.115 --> 02:14.216
-We'll be happy with
whoever you bring over here.
-Absolutely.

02:14.593 --> 02:15.658
Well, good luck.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.637
Alright.
Well, thank you so much.

02:19.265 --> 02:20.722
Congrats.

02:23.644 --> 02:27.646
Congratulations, Hollywood.

02:27.648 --> 02:31.525
-[crying]
-[inhales] Oh, baby, baby.

02:32.736 --> 02:35.195
-[exhales]
-But Hollywood...

02:36.407 --> 02:38.699
We could be parents
within 72 hours.

02:38.701 --> 02:40.384
Lord, are we ready?

02:40.386 --> 02:43.036
I mean, I thought
that we would have
more time to prepare.

02:43.038 --> 02:44.830
Sha, sha...

02:45.833 --> 02:48.542
Baby, we've been wanting this
for a long time.

02:49.420 --> 02:52.421
If we ain't ready,
we gonna get ready.

02:53.132 --> 02:54.381
-[laughs]
-We gonna get ready.

02:54.383 --> 02:56.633
