03:56.737 --> 03:58.237
I can't believe she's gone.

03:59.865 --> 04:01.698
I just wish I had
more time with her.

04:01.700 --> 04:04.326
There was so much more
that I wanted
to talk with her about.

04:05.079 --> 04:06.495
Learn from her.

04:07.164 --> 04:08.205
Well, she's still here.

04:09.583 --> 04:11.041
In your heart, in your blood.

04:13.003 --> 04:15.087
I have put that part of me
on hold for so long.

04:15.089 --> 04:17.631
It gets harder
to hear it, feel it.

04:18.717 --> 04:22.344
I need to spend time out there
and listening.

04:24.306 --> 04:25.547
For her and...

04:28.727 --> 04:31.103
-And for my mother.
-You should do that.

04:32.064 --> 04:33.346
And you don't need
to host today.

04:33.348 --> 04:35.315
They're my friends.
I can find another place.

04:35.317 --> 04:37.818
[giggling]
I'm not missing that.

04:38.821 --> 04:40.362
I want to meet
all your people.

04:41.282 --> 04:43.198
All the folk
who you travel the world with.

04:43.993 --> 04:45.951
Who take you away from me.

04:45.953 --> 04:47.828
No one could ever take me
away from you.

04:48.747 --> 04:50.205
[romantic music playing]

04:59.466 --> 05:00.632
[chuckles softly]

05:01.760 --> 05:03.710
[rockabilly music playing]

05:03.712 --> 05:08.765
Here are your copies
of the final contracts
for your attorney to review.

05:08.767 --> 05:12.060
Well [chuckling] thankfully
I do have good lawyers

05:12.137 --> 05:13.478
who can help me with all this,

05:13.480 --> 05:16.273
'cause honestly
when I read it,

05:16.275 --> 05:18.525
it just all reads
like a foreign language.

05:18.602 --> 05:21.445
[chuckles] Now, the fun part.

05:22.906 --> 05:25.115
We get to taste your recipes.

05:26.201 --> 05:28.243
The lab team has worked hard

05:28.245 --> 05:30.412
to duplicate
the recipes you gave us,

05:30.489 --> 05:33.206
but we can't finalize anything

05:33.917 --> 05:36.543
until we get your approval.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.212
Here's a sneak peek.

05:39.289 --> 05:40.797
[exhales] Alright.

05:49.975 --> 05:51.224
Oh, baby.

05:52.311 --> 05:53.727
It's missing the cinnamon.

05:54.480 --> 05:57.272
There was no cinnamon
in the recipe last...

05:57.274 --> 06:00.525
I told those people.
I don't follow no recipe.

06:00.527 --> 06:02.819
It's... It's all in my head
and in my hand.

06:02.988 --> 06:04.738
I taste as I go.

06:04.740 --> 06:09.534
Um, to mass produce,
we'll just need
to get all that

06:09.536 --> 06:12.704
out of your head
and into a written recipe.

06:12.706 --> 06:14.748
But it's okay.
We'll get there.

06:14.750 --> 06:16.625
It's just a process.

06:16.710 --> 06:17.767
But first...

06:18.754 --> 06:24.925
These are the proposed
pie boxes.

06:27.805 --> 06:31.014
And we plan to place them
at the end of the isle

06:32.017 --> 06:34.309
for maximum visibility.

06:37.356 --> 06:38.647
[breath trembling]

06:40.526 --> 06:41.858
Aren't they great?

06:42.486 --> 06:43.693
They're very nice.

06:45.781 --> 06:48.448
[sighs] Very nice indeed.

06:53.038 --> 06:55.997
Okay, well don't forget
what I said
about the cinnamon.

06:55.999 --> 06:57.416
I can't be out there
not looking right.

06:58.377 --> 06:59.418
I mean, after all...

07:01.713 --> 07:03.380
My face is on these boxes.

07:03.382 --> 07:05.966
-[both laughing]
-It sure is.

07:09.513 --> 07:11.304
This is all that's left
of Momma's legacy.

07:12.057 --> 07:14.516
Momma spent
so much time there.

07:14.518 --> 07:16.518
There's so much about her
that we don't know.

07:17.312 --> 07:19.271
I found this
in Aunt Martha's book.

07:19.347 --> 07:21.273
The green lines represent
all her land.

07:21.275 --> 07:23.400
She left to a praise house
close by.

07:24.236 --> 07:26.820
I mean, I know you didn't have
much time with her,

07:26.822 --> 07:30.907
but to me, she was as real
and present as Daddy was.

07:32.619 --> 07:33.702
Some things.

07:35.914 --> 07:36.955
Not enough.

07:40.419 --> 07:41.609
-Thank you.
-Thanks.

07:44.798 --> 07:48.049
[sighs] I wish
these walls could talk.

07:48.126 --> 07:50.844
[chuckles] For real.

07:52.222 --> 07:53.513
Looking at this,

07:55.267 --> 07:56.892
I realize I spent
a lot of time

07:56.894 --> 07:58.602
living up to his expectations.

08:00.355 --> 08:01.646
I lost track of hers.

08:03.066 --> 08:04.131
How could I let this happen?

08:04.133 --> 08:07.152
[Ralph] Pops had
that effect on us.

08:07.154 --> 08:12.407
It felt like it was a struggle
trying to be who I want to be
and be who he wanted me to be.

08:12.409 --> 08:15.327
[chuckles] I guess
Charley figured it out.

08:15.954 --> 08:17.037
She about the only one

08:17.039 --> 08:18.246
who got it together
in his head.

08:18.323 --> 08:20.749
Mmm, I don't know about that.

08:21.752 --> 08:23.543
I think she disappointed him
less than we did

08:23.545 --> 08:24.911
because she wasn't here
to mess up.

08:24.913 --> 08:27.047
Yeah, well I don't want to
be like that with my kids.

08:28.133 --> 08:30.008
Making them feel like
they can't make mistakes,

08:30.719 --> 08:31.751
be human.

08:32.846 --> 08:36.515
Well, you have to remember
he tried.

08:36.517 --> 08:39.226
And you know, after she died,
he was left with two kids,

08:40.187 --> 08:41.811
a struggling farm
and a broken heart.

08:42.731 --> 08:44.597
He was just surviving.

08:48.028 --> 08:51.279
[Hollywood]
See you all at the debate.
I need your support. Be there.

08:51.356 --> 08:52.447
I hope to see you all
at the debate.

08:52.449 --> 08:54.015
Need your support.

08:54.017 --> 08:56.868
-Yeah.
-Those kids need us more
now than ever before.

08:56.945 --> 08:59.538
So you not only got
Dads on Patrol,

08:59.540 --> 09:00.997
but you're running
for school board too?

09:01.041 --> 09:03.208
Sure am.
Whatever it takes, man.

09:03.285 --> 09:04.960
These schools need
some fixing up.

09:05.420 --> 09:07.337
Yeah well, I don't know why

09:07.339 --> 09:08.421
you have to debate
that sucker.

09:08.423 --> 09:09.923
He's just gonna make a scene.

09:09.925 --> 09:12.008
I mean, you can't reason
with these people.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.385
They got their own
set of facts.

09:13.387 --> 09:14.803
Oh, you're right.
You're right.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.805
But it's a part
of the election process.

09:17.683 --> 09:19.975
And the school board's got
some real power, man.

09:19.977 --> 09:21.226
Now look,
if I can get in there,

09:21.303 --> 09:23.979
then I won't have to do
Dads on Patrol.

09:23.981 --> 09:26.815
I can be able to affect change
from the inside.

09:27.150 --> 09:28.400
We need more power.

09:28.944 --> 09:30.110
And I intend on getting it.

09:30.112 --> 09:32.445
[chuckling]

09:32.447 --> 09:33.780
Anybody with any sense
will know that

09:33.782 --> 09:34.906
you the right man for the job.

09:34.908 --> 09:36.408
You care more about these kids

09:36.410 --> 09:37.600
than some of
their own folks do.

09:37.602 --> 09:38.760
-[cashier] Here you go.
-Thank you.

09:38.837 --> 09:40.561
Well, I appreciate you
for believing in me.

09:40.563 --> 09:43.290
Sandy wants me to pick up
some flyers to pass out
at the hospital.

09:43.292 --> 09:46.042
Well man, here you go.
How are you all settling in?

09:46.086 --> 09:49.796
I love her to the moon,
but I can't find
a thing anymore.

09:49.831 --> 09:51.840
[laughs] I remember
those days, man.

09:52.426 --> 09:54.593
Y'all are so used to
living alone.

09:54.595 --> 09:56.261
It's gonna take some time
getting used to it.

09:56.263 --> 10:00.807
But she rearranged
everything in the house.

10:00.809 --> 10:01.975
[laughing]

10:01.977 --> 10:05.270
And if she didn't move it,
she threw it away.

10:05.347 --> 10:07.981
[both laughing]

10:07.983 --> 10:10.567
Oh man.
I love every second of it.

10:10.611 --> 10:11.610
Uh-huh.

10:11.686 --> 10:14.112
You know,
we're the lucky ones.

10:15.532 --> 10:17.032
Brother, you ain't never lie.

10:23.874 --> 10:24.831
Never lie.

10:27.836 --> 10:29.044
Darla?

10:30.756 --> 10:31.630
[door closes]

10:36.094 --> 10:37.010
What's going on?

10:37.638 --> 10:38.695
Hey.

10:39.723 --> 10:43.224
-[sighs] Is she asleep?
-Yeah.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.311
-How was your day?
-Nothing new.

10:47.397 --> 10:49.564
I stopped by Nova's
to talk about Aunt Martha.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.108
She can't believe she's gone.

10:52.110 --> 10:55.820
Brought back memories
of my mom and my dad

10:56.657 --> 10:58.823
-and just how they were.
-Oh, yeah?

11:01.870 --> 11:02.744
Look, I don't want to fight.

11:03.705 --> 11:04.829
Neither do I.

11:05.791 --> 11:07.707
