not playing fair.

11:29.815 --> 11:31.231
[soft music playing]

11:34.361 --> 11:36.736
-You rang?
-Blue?

11:36.813 --> 11:38.530
What were you doing
hiding in there, man?

11:38.532 --> 11:40.448
Come here. [grunts]

11:40.450 --> 11:43.034
-[laughs]
-Are you happy to see me?

11:43.036 --> 11:44.744
[hums]

11:44.821 --> 11:46.746
[chuckling]

11:46.748 --> 11:48.498
I missed you so much, man.

11:49.209 --> 11:51.334
[Blue] Oh, I missed you too.

11:51.336 --> 11:53.294
You're definitely
not playing fair.

11:53.371 --> 11:54.796
Man, it's good
to see you, boy.

11:58.760 --> 12:00.260
So this is it.

12:00.262 --> 12:02.721
-What you think of
our new home, son?
-It's cool.

12:03.598 --> 12:05.348
-I like it a lot.
-You do?

12:06.184 --> 12:07.475
Even though it's smaller
than the farm?

12:07.477 --> 12:09.644
It's big enough for us.

12:09.646 --> 12:14.232
-Grandma's house is so big
I get lost in it sometimes.
-[chuckles]

12:14.234 --> 12:17.360
Like, I'm on the second floor.
She's on the first floor.

12:17.362 --> 12:19.779
Granddad is in the office
above the--

12:19.781 --> 12:22.073
They have a three-car garage,

12:22.075 --> 12:23.616
but they only have two cars.

12:23.618 --> 12:25.827
You know what they say
about different strokes.

12:25.829 --> 12:27.454
Different strokes
for different folks.

12:28.165 --> 12:30.415
-[chuckling]
-[Blue] Right.

12:32.377 --> 12:33.710
What's this doing here?

12:36.590 --> 12:37.505
Reminding me of home.

12:38.175 --> 12:40.258
And you.

12:40.260 --> 12:41.926
You know, if you ever want
to talk to us, you can, right?

12:44.723 --> 12:46.723
