Who has you smiling?

13:50.372 --> 13:53.414
I'm waiting on a call
from the studio museum.

13:53.416 --> 13:56.751
-[Keke] Mmm-hmm.
-I met a curator there
and sent some of my work.

13:56.753 --> 14:00.004
-So you loved it there?
-I did, yeah.

14:00.882 --> 14:04.968
New York was eye-opening,
you know?

14:04.970 --> 14:07.428
I mean, it's not like
I haven't been there before,
'cause I definitely have,

14:07.430 --> 14:11.057
but something
about this trip was just...

14:12.602 --> 14:14.060
I don't know.
It hit different.

14:14.896 --> 14:16.729
The vibe, the people.

14:17.774 --> 14:18.940
It kind of felt like home.

14:19.901 --> 14:21.401
Or what I want
home to feel like.

14:24.823 --> 14:26.406
Sounds like you have
something to say

14:26.482 --> 14:28.575
and the Keke I know
don't bite her tongue, so...

14:28.577 --> 14:31.661
It's just this is what you do.

14:31.663 --> 14:34.831
Ever since I've met you,
you're always looking
for the next thing.

14:34.833 --> 14:37.000
No, it's not like that.

14:37.043 --> 14:38.960
I went to New York
because I was looking

14:38.962 --> 14:41.504
to secure an investment
for our collective here.

14:41.506 --> 14:43.882
Like, LA is my parents' city.

14:43.884 --> 14:47.886
Like, I grew up there,
but it was their way of life.

14:47.888 --> 14:51.347
